# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in with your actual values.

## Database Configuration

```
# PostgreSQL
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/society_db
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_password
DB_NAME=society_db

# Connection pool
DB_POOL_SIZE=20
DB_MAX_OVERFLOW=20
DB_POOL_RECYCLE=3600
```

## Cache & Message Queue

```
# Redis
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
REDIS_HOST=localhost
REDIS_PORT=6379
REDIS_PASSWORD=
REDIS_DB=0
```

## API Configuration

```
# Backend
API_HOST=0.0.0.0
API_PORT=8000
API_RELOAD=true
API_WORKERS=4
API_LOG_LEVEL=info

# Frontend
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
REACT_APP_API_TIMEOUT=30000
```

## Security

```
# JWT & Authentication
SECRET_KEY=your-super-secret-key-here-generate-random-string
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=15
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS=7

# Session
SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret-key
SESSION_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440

# CORS (comma-separated)
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:8000

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_ENABLED=true
RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=100
RATE_LIMIT_PER_HOUR=1000
```

## External APIs

### Telegram

```
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here
TELEGRAM_BOT_ID=your_bot_id_here
TELEGRAM_API_BASE_URL=https://api.telegram.org
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here
```

### OpenAI / Claude

```
# For GPT/Claude summarization
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...your_openai_key_here...
OPENAI_API_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4
OPENAI_TEMPERATURE=0.7
OPENAI_MAX_TOKENS=500

# Alternative: Claude
CLAUDE_API_KEY=your_claude_api_key_here
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-3-opus-20240229
```

### Email Service

```
# SendGrid
EMAIL_SERVICE=sendgrid
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.your_sendgrid_key_here
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@society-app.com
EMAIL_SENDER_NAME=Society App

# OR: SMTP
# EMAIL_SERVICE=smtp
# SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your_email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your_app_password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@society-app.com

# Email settings
EMAIL_DIGEST_ENABLED=true
EMAIL_DIGEST_TIME=07:00
EMAIL_DIGEST_TIMEZONE=UTC
```

## Logging & Monitoring

```
# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_FORMAT=json
LOG_FILE=logs/app.log
LOG_FILE_MAX_BYTES=10485760
LOG_FILE_BACKUP_COUNT=5

# Error Tracking (Sentry)
SENTRY_DSN=https://your_sentry_dsn_here
SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development
SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=1.0

# Monitoring
MONITORING_ENABLED=true
MONITORING_INTERVAL_SECONDS=60
```

## Feature Flags

```
# Features
TELEGRAM_INTEGRATION_ENABLED=true
AI_DIGEST_ENABLED=true
DEMAND_SUPPLY_ENABLED=true
EMAIL_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=true
PUSH_NOTIFICATIONS_ENABLED=false
TWO_FACTOR_AUTH_ENABLED=false

# Limits
MAX_OFFERS_PER_USER=50
MAX_REQUESTS_PER_USER=20
MAX_FILE_UPLOAD_SIZE_MB=10
MAX_FILES_PER_LISTING=5
```

## Environment

```
# Environment
ENVIRONMENT=development  # development | staging | production
DEBUG=true
TESTING=false

# Version
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
API_VERSION=v1
```

## Frontend Configuration

```
# React
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
REACT_APP_API_TIMEOUT=30000
REACT_APP_LOG_LEVEL=debug
REACT_APP_TELEGRAM_BOT_ID=your_bot_id_here
REACT_APP_SENTRY_DSN=

# Feature flags
REACT_APP_ENABLE_PWA=true
REACT_APP_ENABLE_NOTIFICATIONS=true
REACT_APP_ENABLE_OFFLINE_MODE=true
```

## Payment (Future)

```
# Stripe
STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_...
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...

# PayPal (optional)
PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=
PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET=
```

## S3 / Cloud Storage (Optional)

```
# AWS S3
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=society-app
AWS_S3_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_ENDPOINT=

# Or: DigitalOcean Spaces
DO_SPACES_KEY=
DO_SPACES_SECRET=
DO_SPACES_REGION=
DO_SPACES_BUCKET=
```

## Development Only

```
# Test/Development databases
TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/test_db
SEED_DATABASE=true
CREATE_DEMO_DATA=true

# Development tools
ENABLE_SWAGGER_UI=true
ENABLE_REDOC=true
ENABLE_GRAPHQL_PLAYGROUND=false
```

## Notes

- **Never commit .env files to git** (they're in .gitignore)
- Copy .env.example to .env locally
- Use strong passwords and API keys
- Rotate API keys regularly
- Use different keys for dev, staging, and production
- For production, use environment variable management services (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager)
- Ensure all API keys are never logged

## Example .env File (Development)

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/society_db
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

API_HOST=0.0.0.0
API_PORT=8000
API_RELOAD=true

SECRET_KEY=dev-secret-key-change-in-production
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=15

TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC-DEF1234ghIkl-zyx57W2v1u123ew11
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-xxxxxxxxxxxxx

SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
EMAIL_FROM=dev@society-app.local

ENVIRONMENT=development
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
REACT_APP_LOG_LEVEL=debug
```
